cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS

The paper discusses a new approach to the construction of file signatures for text retrieval, which is a common topic in information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions advances in semantic hashing and dimensionality reduction, which are topics in machine learning (ML) and computer vision (CV), respectively. Hence, cs.LG and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed approach against state-of-the-art search engine algorithms, such as Language models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves indexing and retrieval, which are topics in data structures (DS). Hence, cs.DS is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
